title: upsimples 11x14 Picture Frame Set of 5, Display Pictures 8x10 with Mat or 11x14 Without Mat, Wall Gallery Photo Frames, Black
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Great low-cost option for framing', 'author': 'Daniel', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I love these frames! I don\'t normally write product reviews but these were game changers for me, so I\'d like to offer my thoughts in case anyone else frames often and is seeking a good quality, affordable option.I tried these out as framing options for my digital art. They are very sturdy and well-made for the price - much better constructed than something you\'d find at Michaels in a similar price-range. If you just want a cheap, quick framing option, these are perfect, at least for me. The hardware in back are all good quality. There are two sawtooth hangers that let you hang the piece in either orientation.They do NOT have glass - instead they use an acrylic sheet with film on either side that you peel off before setting into the frame. This keeps the cost low, but it also makes the frames MUCH lighter. This can be an advantage for several reasons - easier and possibly safer to hang, potentially easier or cheaper to ship, won\'t shatter if dropped, etc.I\'m not sure how easy the acrylic might be to scratch (I was very careful when I was peeling off the films and setting into the frames, just in case.) I was also very careful to not touch the acrylic with my fingers if I could help it, in case it left fingerprints that were difficult to wipe away. However, these are normal things you probably already do when working with frames.Other great pros:1. Zero or very little plastic residue from the frames (shavings, dust, etc.) Plastic frames will often have this, but these were very clean.2. Sturdily attached corners, no gaps at the edges. Other "flimsy" frames usually will break, chip, or separate here.3. No warping that I can see anywhere. Clean, straight edges all around.4. Simple smooth finish, sort of in-between glossy and matte. I ordered black frames, but these do come in several colors, which is awesome.5. Last but not least, these come in 8.5"x14", which is a pretty non-standard and often difficult to find size! I REALLY appreciate this, as it\'s what I use for a specific series of art that I create. (Note: FYI, I\'m pretty sure not all colors are available in this size - only black.)Possible cons:1. The acrylic doesn\'t offer any glare resistance as far as I can tell. So depending on where you hang the art, that might be something to consider. That said, they don\'t appear to have any more glare than an average piece of untreated/gallery glass.2. Doesn\'t have a table-stand in back, so you\'re limited to hanging on the wall only.Bottom line: If you just want a very cheap frame for general purposes, or perhaps you are an artist or vendor that frames LOTS of prints or art pieces, these are an excellent low-cost option. I can buy a few packs of these and frame an entire series for a gallery showing, and everything looks perfectly fine AND weighs less to transport. I sincerely hope these frames stick around for good.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 4, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Good frames for a great price', 'author': 'Mike W', 'rating': 5, 'content': "Okay, let‚Äôs get real for a sec. These frames aren't going to be hanging in any galleries anytime soon, but guess what? For what you'd usually shell out on just the sales tax for a fancy frame, you snag yourself six of these bad boys. That's a steal if I've ever seen one.If you're anything like me and have a ton of pics just waiting to find their spot on the wall, this deal is a no-brainer. And hey, they even throw in those picture hangers, which ‚Äì let me tell you ‚Äì are super easy to figure out. No more wrestling with complicated setups.Honestly, for what you're paying, these frames look pretty sleek. They've got this clean vibe that just works with any room. Sure, they're not the kind of frames that'll have people gasping in awe, but they do the job and make your photos look good.All in all, you're getting a bang for your buck here. It's perfect for anyone looking to frame a bunch of pictures without having to dip into their savings. Plus, the easy-peasy hangers? Love that. So, if you're on the hunt for some straightforward, nice-looking frames and an unbeatable deal, you really can't go wrong with these.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 13, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Elegant but inexpensive', 'author': 'BastetCat', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Completely happy with this purchase. You get exactly what you pay for, read the description carefully.The frame and everything else are made of plastic. This means they are lightweight and won\'t break if they fall. It also means they won\'t protect your art from UV damage like glass would, and I\'d rather not more plastic in the environment but I\'m on a fixed budget. So, there are pros and cons.The matte provided isn\'t a real art matte, it\'s just a piece of paper with a hole cut out. Nevertheless, it provides a simulation of the real thing. See my attached photo, with a flower I did in Derwent Inktense pencils for an idea.They were well packaged, and arrived intact. The back opens up easily, and they provide hangers. I have not used the hangers provided yet, so I can\'t provide feedback on them, but I hope they will work on drywall.I\'m poor and I wanted to frame a piece of art I did as an inspiration to do more art. These fit the bill perfectly.Update: I have now used the included plastic hangers. They work GREAT on drywall.I feel the need to address a few things I see in other reviews.The "sticky" sticker - there\'s a thin film of plastic on BOTH sides of the acrylic to protect it from scratches. If you remove this, like the instructions tell you 10x, the sticker comes off. With no residue. Lol.Now in her defense? The film is very thin, and I had trouble seeing it at first too. Go to a corner and drag a finger over it until it pulls off the plastic. Suddenly, the plastic is *much* clearer and brighter! Lol. Magic.The back feels too loose or too tight? Those clips are *adjustable*. They slide back and forth. Slide them back to remove the backing, and slide them forward after you put the clips in place. Maybe I\'ll upload a video.I ordered more of these frames, because they look so good on the wall, and they\'re the best value I could find.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States December 7, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars Affordable frames get the job done', 'author': 'Sierra S', 'rating': 4, 'content': 'Ordered two of 5 pack 8x10 white frames for a photo wall project I had in mind. It turned out beautifully. The frames themselves are decent quality, but nothing super nice. That‚Äôs what I wanted though, because I just wanted a white border so my photos could be the things that truly shine, and that‚Äôs what I got! I gave it 4 stars because I only ended up using the actual frame and the backing, and I removed the plexiglass because it was reflecting way too much light from my window and made the colors of the photos harder to see. All in all though I‚Äôm satisfied with this purchase, for the price it was unbeatable. Just ordered more of these frames for another project in a larger size actually.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States March 2, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect Frames', 'author': 'Savi', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'For me, these frames are perfect: beautiful to look at, light weight, very easy to get pictures in and out of, simple to hang, economical.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 22, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars SLIGHTLY less expensive, but definitely CHEAPER!', 'author': 'T. Anderson', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I bought a set of frames like these a year ago from this manufacturer, and they were an excellent value, well-constructed and obviously of decent quality. I'm not impressed but am willing to accept since the cost is reasonable.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 17, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome Frames', 'author': 'JHL', 'rating': 5, 'content': "These frames look expensive but aren't. Their clean lines and quality construction were exactly what I was looking for in the frames I needed. They were well-packaged as a set of 5 and arrived without any scratches or defects. Very satisfied with this purchase and plan to purchase another set to complete my project!', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 31, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars Lightweight', 'author': 'Frank', 'rating': 4, 'content': "Nice frames. They're lightweight and make an attractive grouping on the wall of my study. I used them with the mats for 8x10 photos and they fit perfectly. I like the plastic cover; it's safer than glass if it should fall or be dropped. However, the frame itself will probably be damaged if it falls off the wall, it has happened to me twice (I have about a dozen of these frames in various sizes). In both cases I was able to coax the frame back into shape with a rubber mallet. The plastic mounting hook supplied with the frames are not great, they break easily (which is why two of the frames fell off the wall), but extra hooks are supplied in the package. Hint: The hooks each have 4 little nails, don't try to hammer them in all at once, use a nail set to tap them in one at a time - it's much easier that way and you won't have to hit it so hard that it causes another picture you just hung to fall down.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 4, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars You get what you paid for', 'author': 'Wen Tsen', 'rating': 4, 'content': "the frames come in five per pack. It comes down to approximately $9 per frame. Price is really cheap, but considering that it's not real wood, it's not even veneer. The frames are made of some kind of engineered material. As for the front clear panel, it's plastic, not glass. At first I was disappointed by the plastic transparent panel, but then I realized that it actually serves a beneficial purpose, in which it will not crack like glass does. that being said, let's hope that the plastic panel will not turn yellow or become cloudy over time. Fingers crossed. Placing the image inside was easy, but the frame is wobbly when trying to hang it on the wall due to its light weight and the attached bracket. To level the frame, I add a small piece of Velcro at the bottom of the frame, and once leveled, I press the velcro into place to secure the frame firmly into its position.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 9, 2024', 'is_verified': True}]

title: Americanflat 12x18 Poster Frame in Black - Photo Frame with Engineered Wood Frame and Polished Plexiglass Cover - Horizontal and Vertical Formats for Wall with Built-in Hanging Hardware
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Overall happy', 'author': 'KP85', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Background: I\'m a semi-pro photographer with more than 15 years of experience, and I have previously worked in a pro frame shop for a short period of time framing flat art of all sizes. I was looking for an inexpensive frame to replace damaged art in a high traffic area of our home.I purchased a 16x16 inch black frame with plexiglass glazing, and I\'m overall happy with this purchase. The frame was well packaged and arrived safely two days after I ordered (with Amazon Prime). The plexiglass had a layer of film on either side to keep it protected and then the frame had styrofoam and cardboard protectors on the corners, was wrapped in plastic, and packaged inside a thin layer of styrofoam in a fitted box. IMO just enough packaging to protect the frame without being excessive. The frame is pre-strung with hangers to orient it vertically or horizontally (kind of unnecessary in this case since the frame is square) and comes with a wire hanger and instructions to attach it. The hanging wire provided is a thicker/stiffer than needed for this application and longer than needed so you do need wire cutters to trim it to size, but it works.Assembling the frame and installing my art was easy. The plexiglass is thin and flexes easily so it needs a little guidance to get it to sit square in the frame rabbet. My plexiglass had a couple small (about 1/4 inch) scratches about 2 inches from the edge (visible before I removed the protective backing), so not perfect but not too large or in a place where it would be conspicuous. The frame itself is nicely assembled, with two "staples" joining each corner and the corners well aligned and flush. You can see a slight seam at two of the corners since the material itself is not black all the way through, but this is only upon examining closely and not noticeable from viewing distance (I didn\'t feel it required any touch up). I found the surface material of the frame to be nicely manufactured - no scratches, dings, bubbling, chips, or other imperfections. I believe the frame is sturdy enough to not warp over time, especially considering the overall light weight of the piece thanks to the plexi glazing.This is a cheap frame with thin plastic glazing. The materials are not archival, the glazing is not optical grade, and its less than $30 for the 16x16 size. For the price, I think it is a great option for inexpensively framing midsize art. If anything, I\'d like to see felt or rubberized bumpers added to the package so that the corners of the frame don\'t rest directly on the wall.The piece we wanted to frame was art that I had commissioned of our pup, and unfortunately the hanger supplied with the original frame failed and resulted in the piece falling to the ground, shattering the glass, breaking the frame, and scratching the original print. Because the art itself was damaged and I have the digital file to reprint it in the future if necessary, I didn\'t want to spend a lot of money on a replacement frame and wasn\'t very concerned about having a perfect optical surface, and this was perfect for safely getting our picture back on our walls. Since the art hangs near our front door and we have a dog and a baby on the way, I actually liked the idea of using plexi and not having to worry about a repeat crash and shatter incident.I think this is a great buy for the money for inexpensive art, and the five star rating I have provided is reflective of the price point and expectations I had for this item. If you have a high value or one of a kind piece you want to last a long time, invest in professional framing and use archival materials and quality UV protective optical glass or acrylic to protect your artwork. If you just want to hang some cheap prints on your walls without spending a ton of money, this is a great option.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States May 15, 2022', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful and big! This frame is not only sleek and stylish but also incredibly practical. The engineered wood frame gives it a modern look, while the polished plexiglass cover adds a touch of sophistication. One thing to note is to remember to take the film off of the plexiglass before displaying your artwork or photo ‚Äì a simple step but important for achieving the best presentation. I particularly love the versatility of this frame, as it comes with both horizontal and vertical hanging formats, making it adaptable to any space. Installing it was a breeze, thanks to the built-in hanging hardware. Once mounted, my artwork looked absolutely amazing within the frame. Overall, I'm thoroughly impressed with the quality and functionality of this poster frame, and I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a stylish and hassle-free way to display their art or photos.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States March 1, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars High value for price, looks great', 'author': 'Oakwood Mt. reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Budget Friendly Frames', 'author': 'Tammy O', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I\'d rate these frames 10-STARS if I could. title: Americanflat 8.5x11 Picture Frame in Black - Use as Diploma Frame or Certificate Frame with Shatter Resistant Glass - Hanging Hardware and Easel Included for Wall and Tabletop Display
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Good inexpensive frame', 'author': 'M. Melvin', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'This is specifically about the "mahogany" option with shatter-resistant glass. The black and white options are 5-packs with plexiglass and I don\'t know anything about those.I got this for a certificate I received at work and it\'s exactly what I was looking for.I\'ll start by saying: this is an inexpensive frame. It\'s obviously not mahogany. It\'s a mahogany-print adhesive veneer on top of ... something that is probably pressboard or similar (I see it\'s called "engineered wood" in the description). I knew it going in and it\'s fine for what I needed.My requirements were:1. Look decent enough for a work certificate2. Real glass3. Not a plastic frame (i.e., cheap wood with a veneer is a-ok for me)4. Arrive unbrokenIt does look nice. Plenty nice enough for this certificate. The veneer is on the nicer end of quality fake wood grain. :) It doesn\'t have any texture but if I needed that I would\'ve paid a WHOLE lot more for a frame with some fancy stained wood. The sides are nice and flat and there are no bubbles in the veneer. Obviously I can\'t say how well that will hold up yet but it\'s enough for my purposes.It has real glass, not some plastic or acrylic layer.Packaging is very good. I seem to have consistent problems with anything fragile coming from Amazon arriving broken. The frame is sealed in shrinkwrap, surrounded on the corners with some quality plastic spacers, and boxed inside a well-fitting box. There were no visible marks anywhere on the frame and the glass was intact. If someone gouges the broad side of it, it\'ll break, but casual delivery abuse probably won\'t.It comes with a stand built into the back for desk use, a black nail hanger pre-attached, and a kit for hanging it by a wire. The wire kit includes a wire and two clips for attachment, and doesn\'t require any nails or staples, and mounts in a way that allows flush hanging on a wall.The back is attached by the usual basic bendable metal tabs one would find on an inexpensive frame.So if you\'re looking for an inexpensive frame that\'s still pretty good (did I mention real glass?), the "mahogany" frame with shatter-resistant is a great option at $13-$15 or so.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States December 18, 2022', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Great frame', 'author': 'Traci M.', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Perfect for certification certificates. title: 18x24 Poster Frame Black - 16x20 Picture Frames with Mat or 18 x 24 without Mat - Polished Plexiglass for Wall Vertically or Horizontally Display - Wall Mounting Hardware Included
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Great product', 'author': 'Travis Knemeyer', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Was a very very minor scratch on one of the 2 frames I ordered other than that these were perfect. Great quality as well.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States August 26, 2022', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Just what we needed', 'author': 'Tav', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Simple but looks nice with the matting', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States December 18, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '1.0 out of 5 stars The packaging is better than the product- Buyer beware !!!', 'author': 'nighthawks', 'rating': 1, 'content': "I did not expect the quality of a handmade frame, nor did my expectations exceed the price point, but this frame is pure junk!! For starters the frame itself is a cheap plastic frame that is far from ridged. Secondly the mat board is not only as thin as paper, it does not seat firmly against your print, so you can expect to see waves on the poster once framed. The worse part, not that the above is not horrible, the mat board is cut WAY TO TIGHT, meaning if you have a 18x24 inch poster, you can not get the mat to cover the edges.. I should also mention the plastic is so thin and glaring, it's just BAD!! I would give this product ZERO stars if I could, and packing this junk back up is just going to waste more time and money,ill pass it on to my kid.. Do yourself a favor, for $20.00 more you can go to a frame shop and get something of value.. So overpriced for what it is and just beyond not acceptable. The people who left this product a higher score than zero must have never gotten a quality frame to know the difference!!", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States August 18, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars Good Frame for the Money', 'author': 'Isaac', 'rating': 4, 'content': "Several high end frame manufacturers are gone, so I'm always searching for alternatives. I post gallery shows of my photographs. Rather than recycling a frame and inserting a different photo (which creates visible wear and tear), I continue to order new frames for new work.This frame is made by ArtToFrame. The distributor got it to me within a week.It was well packed -- no damage. It is made of solid wood NOT pressed board. The plexiglass is just the right thickness, and is protected on both sides by peel-away sheeting. No scratches (Make sure you have your canned air and static brush nearby).THIS FRAME WILL FIT THE PLEXI, YOUR SINGLEWEIGHT MATTED ARTWORK AND YOUR SINGLEWEIGHT BACKING BOARD. Repurpose the original cardboard sheet to protect the front if storing/shipping.The closure tabs are good -- none of them snapped, but be careful not to open and close them a lot.The wood screws included with the hanging eyelets are too long for my liking (minus 1/2 star) so I used shorter ones. Just pick your mounting spots and use a hand awl to start the screw holes.The hanging wire, hook and nail are all sufficient -- this is a lightweight frame.One criticism: The corner joints are stapled from the back -- not very sturdy. I would pay a few dollars more for better constructed corners (Minus 1/2 star).", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States May 5, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Great frame for crafters', 'author': 'gail s.', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'This is a really "all in one" frame. It has the mat, the plastic (rather than heavy glass), hangers for vertical or horizontal hanging, and easy clips fpr attaching the back. Love it for its ease. I didn\'t want to cut the prop off in case I decided to use them differently down the road. I ended up finding the best way to hang them was to put the back on upside down so the bottom of the prop is at the top of the frame; it seemed to help them be tighter to the wall and made easier to get them straight.Now the white frames were a different story. I ordered Amazon\'s used product; it was reported that the only issue was that it would not come in original packaging but that the product itself was not damaged. This was not the case. The corners did not match up correctly so although they looked okay at a glance there was actually a gap at the mitered corners on both frames to the point light easily came through. Also the gold distressing wasn\'t as nicely done on the white frames I received. The box was fine, so it had to be packaged with a dent in the side of the frame causing a one inch part to chip loose. Overall the rest of the frame is really nice , so I decided to keep the frame and repair it myself. Will I order another frame from this dealer for my next puzzle? The answer is yes. The frame is that good.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 27, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Exact fit for Ceaco 1000 piece puzzle', 'author': 'Peter R. Robinson', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Was an exact fit for a 1000 piece Ceaco puzzle that has advertised dimensions of 26.6" x 19" (68CM x 48CM). Good bang for the buck. Came with white gloss sheet in case you need a border for smalller pictures or puzzles. But if your picture or puzzle is smaller, you would have to adhere it to the border sheet to prevent it sliding down. In my case where I had an exact fit, this is what I did. On the rear of the frame, I bent the retaining tabs that hold everything into the frame vertically and removed everything from the frame. I then removed the backing from both sides of the transparent sheet, and placed it on top the puzzle, which was already on a piece of cardboard which I built it on. Putting the transparent sheet onto the puzzle first helps to stiffen the puzzle to slide it onto the backing sheet. (I discarded the white background sheet as I did not need a border) Then I slid the puzzle and transparent sheet over onto the backing sheet that came with the frame and lined up the edges. Next, I placed a spacer on the table (I used a banker\'s box cover which is about 2" high, but you can use anything about that height), and placed the backing sheet, puzzle and transparent sheet on top of it, then rechecked that all edges are aligned. Then I put the frame over it carefully to avoid snagging the edges, and once it was completely seated over everything, I felt under along the edges and bent the tabs onto the backing sheet. Once I got them all, I flipped it over and pressed them as snugly as possible. Done!', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 15, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '3.0 out of 5 stars Misrepresented item and worthless customer service', 'author': 'Chef Charley', 'rating': 3, 'content': "I purchased the 5x10 frame and paid more then other listings for it because it did not have the easel style table top stand on the back as I intended to use it to frame an item for a gift. When I received it, the backing looked nothing like the listing. It had the easel style stand and unlike the photo on the listing, had really cheap and misaligned ring style hangers. Unfortunately, I needed it now so I'm stuck with the wrong style of frame. I messaged them which they replied, oh thank you for reminding us that we needed to update that, please enjoy 5% off the purchase of another one of our items. The frame itself is cheap trash. I could have gotten 2 of this same frame in another listing for the same price if I knew that they were going to send one with the backer I didn't want in the first place. Disappointing junk.Edit-After the review, they refunded my money so I gave them back a star. You can get this same frame in a two pack from other sellers for the same price as their one.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States November 22, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect puzzle frame', 'author': 'Laura Clift', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'I was thoroughly happy with the quality of this frame. Add to that they are inexpensive and so lightweight you can mount with Velcro tack strips. No glass, instead lightweight clear plastic and low profile makes for safe and easy mounting. A quick Amazon search and you can get inexpensive card inserts that you can use particularly in larger frames with a craft knife and a little patience to make your own custom collage frames for a fraction of the cost. One of my favorite purchases for my new home in making the space personalized and home for a really low cost yet still looks great!! title: The Frame
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Obliterates the Fourth Wall', 'author': 'Happy Camper', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Had not heard of this movie before seeing it listed on Prime and was deeply and pleasantly surprised by it. Also surprised it came out in 2014. If you are a fan of Andrei Tarkovsky\'s work then you may enjoy this film. It has a slight Kubrick vibe to it as well, but more Tarkovsky I think. The Frame reminds me a lot of Tarkovsky\'s "Stalker," which is a masterpiece from 1979. Not only does Winans (director of The Frame) do wonders with not just the fourth wall but with the frame as well (kudos to the editors), but brings the viewer into the frame in some very mind-blowing ways. The film is somewhat dark, but more in a psychological sense. I look forward to watching it again, and probably again and again. Great work!', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States March 23, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars Definitely NOT boring!', 'author': 'lisa bee', 'rating': 4, 'content': "This movie isn't maybe amazing, but it is interesting. Not boring in the least and certainly not hard to follow. It is sort of like another movie where the author writes the character except there is no author. But the story is being written none the less. If you like different & interesting films this is for YOU! :)", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States May 3, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Masterpiece!', 'author': 'Joseph B.', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'A story that is unafraid to examine the big concepts of life, death and existence. To manage such ambitious goals without a hint of pretentiousness, all the while unfolding a tale that is absorbing, entertaining and filled with unexpected twists, can only leave one marveling at the genius of the storytellers. I found "The Frame" to be a uniquely satisfying cinematic experience - one that I won\'t soon forget.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States April 24, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '1.0 out of 5 stars SO BORING....DRAGS ON FOREVER', 'author': 'STEVE', 'rating': 1, 'content': 'Movie sucks, so boring. reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Terrific film!', 'author': 'Movie Guy', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'WOW! What a little gem of a film! This was such a fun ride! I really liked the actors! There are a lot of homages to enjoy with this one, the acting is good, and so is the overall direction and production value. A solid 3 1/2-star movie out of five.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States May 19, 2021', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '1.0 out of 5 stars Yawnfest', 'author': 'Sparkle Pants - Real Reviewer in US', 'rating': 1, 'content': 'I feel like they were trying to make some sort of point about "violation of privacy" because they said "violation of privacy" about 80 times throughout the movie.Aside from that it was boring as heck.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States August 14, 2021', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Great Film!!!', 'author': 'Amazon Customer', 'rating': 5, 'content': "It's rare when any movie, be it an indie film or a major studio production, puts it all together. You'll love it.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States August 19, 2021', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': "5.0 out of 5 stars I'm a fool for a well-written plot line and this movie delivers.", 'author': 'KB', 'rating': 5, 'content': "I'm a fool for a well-written plot line and this movie delivers. I don't want to spoil the film for you but this modern drama has a plot twist that will draw you in and leave you waiting for the conclusion. The actors are quite good and the dialogue is believable. You won't be wasting your time with this one.", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States May 20, 2021', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': "3.0 out of 5 stars Don't call it Voyeurism......okay, yeah, call it Voyeurism", 'author': 'John Smistad', 'rating': 3, 'content': 'The new British thriller "Framed" covers a lot of ground. Privacy issues, single female self-sufficiency/independence (as ardently advocated by a fetching Lottie Amor, who needs to be in more movies), frank confirmation that men really do want what woman say men really want aaaand a political scandal tossed in for good measure is plenty to process.The good news is that, all in all, this portrait of a guy (Thomas Law of BBC-TV\'s "EastEnders") going gaga over a gorgeous neighbor gal through his camera lenses does a summarily snappy job of focusing in on each of these developing plot lines.Labeled a thriller, "Framed" is not so much that as it is an intelligent investigation of the legal and moral boundaries of personal privacy, along with accepting accountability for one\'s actions, regardless of political standing or status in the social strata.However, in the end, what we really have here is a good old-fashioned love story, featuring a fabulously photogenic young couple.No matter how they\'re framed.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States May 21, 2021', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars The movie "Framed" covers the right to privacy and protecting your own identity!', 'author': 'Michelle Finn', 'rating': 4, 'content': 'When you are in a compromising situation that a stranger sees as an opportunity to take advantage, how will you know to be diligent in verifying what you believe is the truth? Falling for a misleading note with no name or identifiable fact, who are you in communication with? An educational and thought provoking lesson on identity/reputation damage. If you trust the wrong person, what is the cost to your personal life?', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States July 31, 2021', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Well Acted Indie Drama', 'author': 'JGReviews', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Framed is a well acted and well directed indie drama. The setup had a hint of Rear Window, which I love, and it really was a fresh and distinct film, full of intrigue, ambiguity, and morality questions. An interesting watch for those in the mood for a good indie film.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States May 4, 2021', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars A welcome surprise', 'author': 'Adrian L.', 'rating': 4, 'content': 'I enjoyed this movie very much. It is well-written and crafted beautifully from top to bottom. It has a small cast and minimal locations but it felt bigger than the individual pieces. The direction, cinematography, production design and editing were very reserved and, frankly, I loved the approach. The lead male and female were charming and had a great chemistry. This is a very good movie and I highly recommend it.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States August 19, 2021', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '4.0 out of 5 stars Great on-screen chemistry', 'author': 'Bill Cragmont', 'rating': 4, 'content': 'I really liked this film and enjoyed the flirty, light, friendly, sexy, banter between the two attractive leads. title: The Frame
reviews: [{'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Obliterates the Fourth Wall', 'author': 'Happy Camper', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Had not heard of this movie before seeing it listed on Prime and was deeply and pleasantly surprised by it. Not only does Winans (director of The Frame) do wonders with not just the fourth wall but with the frame as well (kudos to the editors), but brings the viewer into the frame in some very mind-blowing ways. The frame is that good.', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States February 27, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Exact fit for Ceaco 1000 piece puzzle', 'author': 'Peter R. Robinson', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'Was an exact fit for a 1000 piece Ceaco puzzle that has advertised dimensions of 26.6" x 19" (68CM x 48CM). Good bang for the buck. Came with white gloss sheet in case you need a border for smalller pictures or puzzles. But if your picture or puzzle is smaller, you would have to adhere it to the border sheet to prevent it sliding down. In my case where I had an exact fit, this is what I did. On the rear of the frame, I bent the retaining tabs that hold everything into the frame vertically and removed everything from the frame. I then removed the backing from both sides of the transparent sheet, and placed it on top the puzzle, which was already on a piece of cardboard which I built it on. Putting the transparent sheet onto the puzzle first helps to stiffen the puzzle to slide it onto the backing sheet. (I discarded the white background sheet as I did not need a border) Then I slid the puzzle and transparent sheet over onto the backing sheet that came with the frame and lined up the edges. Next, I placed a spacer on the table (I used a banker\'s box cover which is about 2" high, but you can use anything about that height), and placed the backing sheet, puzzle and transparent sheet on top of it, then rechecked that all edges are aligned. Then I put the frame over it carefully to avoid snagging the edges, and once it was completely seated over everything, I felt under along the edges and bent the tabs onto the backing sheet. Once I got them all, I flipped it over and pressed them as snugly as possible. Done!', 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States January 15, 2024', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '3.0 out of 5 stars Misrepresented item and worthless customer service', 'author': 'Chef Charley', 'rating': 3, 'content': "I purchased the 5x10 frame and paid more then other listings for it because it did not have the easel style table top stand on the back as I intended to use it to frame an item for a gift. I measured the frame and it came out as 8" x 8", when I ordered a 10X10. Then I used my tape measure and saw that although the tape measure "inches" are divided into 1/8" sections, the inch is actually 10/8 of an inch. Kind of funny and still worked for what I needed.) Note that the frame is 1" in depth, so the picture will not hang tight to the wall. There is a slot at the top for the pieces of glass to slide into. The installation kit comes with little clips to hold the glass together. The kit also comes with some funky nails. As you tap them into the wall, the nail part slides further into the plastic piece. Two panes of glass with polished edges, so no cutting your hands while handing. Comes with an amazing kit (photo #1) that includes step-by-step instructions, and everything that makes preparing your art quite easy - including a little level, pencil, tape measure, glass cleaning cloth, and gloves (which make it easy to handle the glass without filling it with fingerprints), and options for attaching to the wall including screws with anchors or hammer tacks - all in a nifty plastic case. The kit is worth $10 alone. You do have to attach the hanging clip to the frame yourself (you\'ll need a philips screwdriver), but that way you can choose whether the frame will hang portrait or landscape orientation (see photos 2-3). Tip #1 - Don\'t use the glue dots that come in the kit to affix your art to the bottom glass (as a means of positioning it so it doesn\'t move around). I found that where the glue dots were placed, they created a \'bump\', and when pressed against the top glass and placed in the frame, those areas stuck to the top glass and were very noticeable. After seeing this and not being happy, I removed the glue dots (a pain) and instead used tiny pieces of double-sided Scotch tape to hold my art in position to the bottom glass. Much better. Tip #2 - Note that the 2 panes of glass slide into a slot cut into one of the11" sides of the frame. Once assembled, you then insert clips over the glass to prevent the glass from slipping out (see photo 4). This works best for portrait landscape, because you can hang with slot to the top (and you won\'t see the slot or clips). But with landscape art, one of the sides will show the slot (photo 4). If you know in advance where you\'ll be hanging the landscape photo, you can attach the hanging clip so that the side slot and clips are in the least noticeable position, unless of course this doesn\'t bother you like it did me. I am really happy with the results. Kudos to MEDOG for their specialization in frames (gotta love that video of their factory) and at a better quality than today's average anywhere else, aside from a specialty framing shop (this old photo did not rise to that occasion).Ë∞¢Ë∞¢", 'timestamp': 'Reviewed in the United States November 29, 2023', 'is_verified': True}, {'title': '5.0 out of 5 stars Inexpensive, good looking frame', 'author': 'Icewalker', 'rating': 5, 'content': 'The frame is plastic, but at this price-point that\'s fine with me. If you want MDF (fiber board) or real wood, look elsewhere. Although either.of MDF and/or wood will be more expensive.Also, know that the "glass" isn\'t real glass but a VERY clear plexiglass type material. That is a BIG plus for me. If you\'ve ever had a frame fall to the floor as I have and the glass shatter with minute glass shards going everywhere, you might consider it a plus too. I now specifically look for frames that DON\'T have glass. If you want glass, look elsewhere.The backing is a quality thickness with spring tabes that fit under a grove in the frame. These are much better than metal tabs stuck into the frame that you have to bend down onto the back. I like that it offers a few different display options. The glass area is about 5x7", so you can use a rectangular photo that is 4x6 (or smaller) and have a small transparent margin, no mat required. Or you can use a 5x7 rectangular photo, in which case it looks like a regular frame again. Or you can insert something of an irregular shape and showcase it, such as a leaf, or a memorable flat object, or a collage of mementos, or a paper with rough edges.The wood is a great color, it matches very well with some other oak frames I have acquired recently. The woodworking is smooth and the grain looks nice, and there are two sawtooth hangers already mounted on back. Inside it has two sheets of real glass, so the frame is fairly heavy for its size, and needs careful handling. When you insert something inbetween the glass, you\'ll probably need to use some tape to hold it in position against the back sheet of glass.The glass slides out of one side, and it uses a strip of rope to hold it in place. I appreciate the ingenuity there, though it is a bit unexpected to look at. The rope color is a fair match for the wood and though it is visible, it\'s not distracting. If you hang the frame in portrait orientation you may not see the rope. The rope seems to unravel very slightly each time you slide it in and out, but fortunately it\'s very easy to replace if you ever needed to in the future.The only real drawback I encountered on mine is that the mounting hardware for the horizontal orientation was installed off center a bit. I\'ll still able to hang it with balance, but I need to use one of the sawtooth slots other than the center one.
